wikipedia_page.main: Rear-Admiral Sir Frederick Lewis Maitland  (7 September 1777 – 30 November 1839) was an officer in the Royal Navy during the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars.  He rose to the rank of rear admiral and held a number of commands.  The most famous event of his career occurred when Napoleon Bonaparte surrendered to him aboard HMS Bellerophon, marking the final end of the Napoleonic Wars.
